current.about: Margot Lévêque is a French Graphic and Type Designer currently based in Paris. She specialized in Type Design, Branding, Web & Editorial Design. After gaining experiences in Paris and Amsterdam, she spent a few months working at Pentagram in New-York with Paula Scher. She's currently an independent graphic designer working with clients like Hermès Paris, Vogue, Louis Vuitton, &Walsh, Studio Nari, etc. across the fields of fashion, music, art and more.

settings.title: Phoebe Tonkin
settings.text: Custom logotype for Phoebe Tonkin. LESJOUR! (pronounced leisure), is a new way of thinking about dressing, inspired by the leisure suits of the ‘70s—a wardrobe staple that’s as versatile as it is chic. Each piece is handmade in LA.

settings.title: Modular
settings.text: @modularbymensah is a sculptural furniture designer based in London. We created Modular to represent this ethos, exploring how a typeface can take on human forms, whilst also feeling modular at its core. Modular has bespoke glyphs for specific characters that allow the characters to adapt depending on the space they are trying to fill. Created in collaboration with Studio Nari.

settings.title: Threads of fate
settings.text: Aura is a bespoke typeface created for Threads of Fate. An oracle and tarot deck producer in Los Angeles. The typeface was created to hold symbols in the counters of the characters as well as have hidden graphic motifs embedded in the character builds. Soft and sharp shapes juxtapose to create a sense of movement and elegance within each character. {more}

settings.about:
Margot Lévêque is a French Type Designer and Type Strategist currently based in New York. She has a solid knowledge in the typography field and helps brands create unique typography with a honed design aesthetic. This process includes a custom logo, bespoke typefaces and type design advisements.


After graduating from a design school in Paris with an Art Direction and Type Designer Master’s Degree, Margot went on to work with prestigious agencies and fashion labels including Vogue, Louis Vuitton, Pentagram, Prada, A24, &Walsh and Hermès Paris, and work closely with famous clients such as Phoebe Tonkin, Ariana Grande and Emma Chamberlain. 


Elegance, creativity, invention & beauty: That’s how Margot Leveque defines her process. She is working worldwide mainly with fashion, skincare, art, hotel and music brands and also offers creative consultancy, working closely with people to elevate their own brands.

studio@margotleveque.com

settings.title: Romie Italic
settings.description:
Romie is a typeface designed by Margot Lévêque. Started in 2017, this typeface is a display born from calligraphy. It covers a majority of the european languages and comes in the standard file formats (for print & web). Romie has been updated in 2022: the glyphset has been expanded, including its mythical large ligatures set. Romie is now available in Regular, Regular Italic, Medium, Bold and Black. The others italics will be released very soon!

Many thanks to Guillaume Besson for his help in development, production and for all the support during the release rush! Special + Another special thanks to Céline Hurka for her help in development.

settings.title: Romie Regular
settings.description:
Romie, a calligraphy-inspired display font by Margot Lévêque, carries forward the rich legacy of influences from Lubalin and Bookman.

It supports over 300 languages from all over the world, including most European languages, a number of languages from the Americas and Africa, as well as Vietnamese. It's available in 12 styles total. An update in June 2024 includes all italic styles, thus completing the Romie family. Mastering, development, and production were expertly directed by José Solé.


Note: For those who have already purchased the Romie family, please contact us to receive a promo code to purchase the rest of the family.

settings.title: Kalice Regular
settings.description:
Designed by Margot Lévêque in 2018, Kalice underwent a transformative 2023 update, encompassing additional weights and elegant italic styles, all designed by Margot herself. We extend our gratitude to the dedicated production and mastering team: Weltkern, Ibrahim Kaçtıoğlu, and Jan Charvát.

A revival of the Elzévir Anglais typeface from Turlot Foundry, Kalice offers clean lines and a modern look, perfect for headlines, logos, and graphic design projects. It supports various European languages and is available in standard formats (otf, woff, and woff2). For details, request the Kalice Specimen.

settings.title: Ninna Regular
settings.description:
Ninna is a display typeface that balances a contemporary aesthetic with a deep respect for classical heritage, drawing inspiration from the French Decorative Arts. Designed between 2019 and 2024, it features a range of weights from Book to Black with matching italics. Classical forms and expressive swash alternates bring sophistication to headlines, branding, and text, while its delicate contrast and generous x-height ensure readability. Dynamic italics add boldness and character, making Ninna a versatile choice for both display and editorial use. PDF of the full glyphset available upon request.

Design: Margot Lévêque

Help in Production: Fanny Hamelin, Tania Chacana


Mastering: José Solé


Years of Creation: 2019–2024

settings.question:
Hi Margot! First question:

How can I use your fonts as a student?
settings.answer: We offer discounted licenses for students to use fonts in both personal and commercial projects during their studies. After graduation, personal projects started as a student can still use these fonts, but client projects will require a separate license. Teachers at accredited institutions can also access discounted fonts for teaching and non-commercial class projects. The student font pack includes an educational license that covers various media types.

settings.question: Can I modify your fonts ?
settings.answer: Direct modifications to the font files are strictly prohibited and violate our EULA (End User License Agreement). Any unauthorized changes may result in legal action. To avoid such issues, we strongly encourage you to contact us directly so we can discuss your specific needs and find an appropriate solution together! studio@margotleveque.com

settings.question: What’s your licensing model?
settings.answer:
Our licensing is straightforward: we provide a single, comprehensive license that covers ALL applications, including desktop, web, print, app usage... Pricing is determined by one simple metric: the total size of your company. This is calculated based on the total number of employees in your organization, not the number of users who will directly work with our fonts.

With every license, you’ll receive both WOFF and OTF file formats to meet your needs seamlessly.

settings.question: What is your refund policy?
settings.answer: Unfortunately, we cannot provide refunds for any font purchases. Once a font has been purchased, it is considered a final sale.

settings.question: What about trial licenses?
settings.answer: We provide a unique and complimentary trial license to our fonts, which enables users to evaluate and test the font software for the purpose of creating test documents, visuals, and web pages, as well as presenting them to clients or other interested parties. Our font files contain all the glyphs, making it easier for users to pitch projects, test the final font, and save time and effort.

settings.question: Okay, so... Can I use it for free?
settings.answer:
This trial license is intended for professionals to test the fonts internally only. However, it’s essential to note that all licensing terms and conditions must be strictly followed. Any external, commercial, or public use of the trial fonts is strictly prohibited.

Please be aware that our team conducts regular checks, and if we discover any websites or projects misusing trial fonts, we will take immediate legal action with our legal team to address the violation.

settings.question: I’m a designer working on a project for a company. Who should buy the license?
settings.answer: The company is the sole license holder, but you can purchase the font files on behalf of your client as a payment facilitator. This option can save your client time and effort, allowing them to focus on their core business activities. However, it’s important to note that your client remains responsible for adhering to the licensing terms and conditions.

settings.question:
I bought a license before, but since then the size of my company has changed. 

Do I need to upgrade my license?
settings.answer: To ensure that your license is up to date, regular checks are carried out on our side. Therefore, it is important to contact us to upgrade your fonts and keep your license valid.

settings.question: Do I need to pay again for the update of one of your fonts?
settings.answer: Of course not! If you have purchased a license before and an update is available, you are entitled to it for free. Normally, you will receive it automatically. If you don’t receive it, don’t hesitate to contact us at studio@margotleveque.com.
